lead_paragraph: Stefan Küng staged a stunning comeback to upset the world-record holder Jack Bobridge and win the men’s individual pursuit final at the track cycling world championships in Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines, France.

headline.main: Record Holder Jack Bobridge Falls in Upset

snippet: Stefan Küng staged a stunning comeback to upset the world-record holder Jack Bobridge and win the men’s individual pursuit final at the track cycling world championships in Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines, France.
